values: 2 years to the day.  my god so much has changed... maybe i will keep up again... but probly not.

A WOMAN SHOULD HAVE

              .....one old love
              she can imagine
              going back to...
              and one who reminds
             her how far she has come...

A WOMAN SHOULD HAVE

             .....enough money within her
             control to move out and
             rent a place of her own
             even if she never wants
             to or needs to...

A WOMAN SHOULD HAVE

              .....something perfect to wear if
              the employer or date of her dreams
              wants to see her in an hour...

 A WOMAN SHOULD HAVE

              .....a youth she's content
              to leave behind....

 A WOMAN SHOULD HAVE

             .....a past juicy enough that
              she's looking forward to
              retelling it in her old age....

A WOMAN SHOULD HAVE

            .....a set of screwdrivers, a
            cordless drill, and a black
            lace bra...

A WOMAN SHOULD HAVE

           .....one friend who always makes
           her laugh... and one who lets
           her cry...

A WOMAN SHOULD HAVE

          .....a good piece of furniture
          not previously owned by anyone
          else in her family...

A WOMAN SHOULD HAVE

            .....eight matching plates, wine
            glasses with stems, and a recipe
            for a meal that will make her
            guests feel honored..

A WOMAN SHOULD HAVE

             .....a feeling of control over
             her destiny...

EVERY WOMAN SHOULD KNOW...
             
              .....how to fall in love without
              losing herself...

EVERY WOMAN SHOULD KNOW...

             .....HOW TO QUIT A JOB,
             BREAK UP WITH A LOVER,
             AND CONFRONT A FRIEND
             WITHOUT RUINING THE FRIENDSHIP...

EVERY WOMAN SHOULD KNOW...

             .....when to try harder... and
             WHEN TO WALK AWAY...

EVERY WOMAN SHOULD KNOW...

            .....that she can't change the
            length of her calves, the width
            of her hips, or the nature of her
            parents...
EVERY WOMAN SHOULD KNOW...

             .....that her childhood may not
             have been perfect...but its
             over...

EVERY WOMAN SHOULD KNOW...

         .....what she would and wouldn't
          do for love or more...

EVERY WOMAN SHOULD KNOW...

           .....how to live alone... even if
            she doesn't like it...

EVERY WOMAN SHOULD KNOW...

           .....whom she can trust,
           whom she can't,
           and why she shouldn't
           take it personally...

EVERY WOMAN SHOULD KNOW...

         .....where to go...
        be it to her best friend's kitchen table...
        or a charming inn in the woods...
        when her soul needs soothing...

EVERY WOMAN SHOULD KNOW...

            .....what she can and can't
            accomplish in a day...
            a month...and a year...

Yes.  So.  Hmm. Lastnight at about 10 - 1030 Akira informed me that he just wants to be friends.  -At least thats what i think he said...- but none the less he used the terms "i have a tendency to slip" and "I dont wanna ruin anything cuz face it... we're awesome friends".  That's not good enough.  I dont even want to be friends with him.  I ACTUALLY HONESTLY thought -yeah that's where I went wrong... I thought- that he really wanted to be with me and that he -I dont know.  All I can say is 'HOW INCREDIBLY STUPID ARE YOU AMANDA???'.  I am a little numb right now.  I dont know what to say or how to say it.  I almost started crying in front of him.  Thank God I didnt.  I start to realize now that he never really liked me.  He only wanted a piece of ass and when he realized that isnt all that I wanted he breaks shit off.  WHAT THE FUCK EVER.  ...if that boy only knew...

Technically my day started last night.  My dad's truck broke down on me.  I am a sissy girl... I dont know what the fuck is wrong with it but just thinking about it make me infuriated - if that really is a word. My parents keep asking 'well, what's wrong with it?' and OMG I think that if I hear that one more time I will scream and choke someone's neck.  The way I see it is that if I actually knew what was wrong with it I wouldn't be in this shit canoe and I would have fixed it.  But as my mom pointed out to me this morning, you dont very well go to the doctor's when you are sick and say "I dont know what's wrong just fix it".  I finally got home last night at about 3 am but I didn't fall asleep until approximately 4 am.  I had to get up for an overseas screening at 7 am.  *For y'all who are unaware, My parent's and my brother are moving to gay-tard Japan*  The icing on the cake is when they made me get on the scale.  Talk about LARD ASS.  And everything has just spiraled down from there.  I feel about as nasty as it gets.  I hate myself for letting me just lose control over something that was going so well for the longest time.  I truly dont understand how I can wonder why guys dont like me when I look like this.  Even as I sit here I want to eat.  That's all I ever want to do.  Stuff my fat fucking face.  I make myself sick.  When did I turn into something that I hate? Why is it that the only thing I can seem to do these days with confidence is cry? I am not going back to dance.  I can't.  I let myself down.  I need to stop being such a sissy.

so like i said... i havent been on here in a grip.  i think that i should start back up.  my life is making a lot more sence these days and all is well in the land of stink and fruit flies.  haha thats hilarious!  I have been talking to Cortney a lot lately and it makes me happy.  I like being still connected to Ridgiecresto.  I really wish that I was there right now.  I miss my friends and I miss Jimmy and I miss Nicole and I miss Cortney and I miss Del Taco and shit really I could just go on and on...  I want to go down for a visit.
so I am planning on sending Cortney up here.  I cant wait but it seems like the world is against me in my endeavor.  My dad is gone and I keep having to fix bullshit on the truck.  I think that I am going to buy a new car.  I hope.  I want a cute white one.  or a navy blue one.  or a red one. or a black one.  or one that just works.  haha!
Havent talked to Kirk in FOREVER. eh.  It was good while it lasted.  Talked to Ryan a few weeks ago.  God he makes me smile. I really should go and see him... *smile* :0) and I called Stevie on his b-day!  Yay for mah bestest buddie Stevie!!  Woop woop.
Havent been on here in a while... I kinda miss it but unfortunately I dont have a whole mess of time in my life.... work sucks and I think that I am gonna find a new job.

I havent been updating lately and I feel a little bit guilty about it... okay yeah so I havent really... I am not going back to Cali right yet.   I am getting my life squared away here and it is a really good feeling.  I am glad that Nicole is supportive of my choice.  I talked to my ex Kevin tonight.  God.  I hate being boyfriend-less because it makes me want to hook up with old flames.  But Really I need to move on with the new.  -If I find someone patient and perfect for me... He doesnt have to be 'perfect'... just perfect for me.   as if that made any sence.   my mother and I have been getting along a lot better these days.  I attribute it to the fact that I am never really home any more.  I have been kickin it with my newest greatest friend Morgan.  I love  her!!  She is just like me.  It is so fuckin crazy!!  I also luuuuvvv my newest bestest friend Megan!  She is sooo much fun.  Life is definately good right now.   I really want to start taking violin lessons.  It is such a beautiful instrument.  sigh.  Im drunk.  I have been drinking a lot lately. and I am rambling.  GOD BLESS LONG ISLAND AND THEIR ICED TEAS.  lol  Much luv to you all and to all a fab-u-fuckin-lous night!

Yeah... so I picked up my brother right on schedule and he was out there waiting for me.  We had to run back home cuz he forgot his headgear -poor kid- and then we went to the orthodontists office.  Nothing exciting happened.  I sat in the waiting room for 15 minutes and then we were done.  Then I went to the post office and then we drove down by the beach...(gotta love living on an island).  TA DA.  thats is.  I was highly disappointed.



Tonight...is a new episode of Dawson's Creek.  I cant believe that my favorite show ends this year.  It's like a small part of my life is over.  The only thing that I have that has been consistant since high school.  That and my friendship with Nicole.  I guess that after 2 damn years its time to let go of hs.  But it hurts me so.  Agh.  


I need a boyfriend.  Someone to love on.  I miss Jimmy :(  I miss kirk being all lovey with me.  Fuck  I even miss fun Bobby.

Today... I am feeling a little bit rowdy.  I dont like getting up early.... if you can consider 930 early.  -I do.  Im used to 100.  I bought some unisom to help me sleep a lil at night... I cant really decide if it really works.  I went to bed earlier than usual but I just kinda layed there for a bit.  I finally fell asleep.  Are those things addictive?  


Today...I get to take my brother to the orthodontist.  I am sure there will be some sort of adventure as there always is with my brother.  I will let you guys know if there are any when I get back

Okay so Eric, Mah buddie-pal  said that I should just add ppl to my list.  I dont think its gonna work but he told me to add these certain ppl... Aparently ones from spain!  Sweet Deal.  Too bad I was never in Moron.




*WISH ME LUCK!*

Today... was good.  My academic advisor was sooo nice and she walked me through all the steps I would need to get transferred and also informed me that people usually got a Masters in Architecture and that I could go Pre-Arch.  So now I am just a tiddle bit scared because what if I decide that I dont want to do it... AHHH.  So now Im just kinda confused but at least I am in PRE CALCULUS II.  I feel so smart!  Smarter than when I tested into Algebra and Trig 2.  If anyone feels like throwing some ideas at me to get me moving then by all means.  But keep in mind that I DO NOT WANT TO BE A TEACHER OF ANY SORT.  


I found these pics last night of when I had really long ass hair.  wow.  I never realized how long it actually was.  Reminds me of highschool.  Good Times.  I am so glad Nicole and I are still friends

Dont ask me why I am writing in this thing yet again cuz I honestly dont know.  For some reason I feel like I have left a lot unsaid.  Tomorrow I go and talk to an Academic Advisor.  Lol What if she says to me: "Ms. Chenard... Im sorry.  We cant help you.  You are too lost and confused for your own damn good.  Please try again when you can figure shit out"?

You know I really have to stop watching Dawson's Creek.  I love that show so much though it's not even funny.  Sometime's I feel like I totally relate to the show but then like I do something psycho like get all protective over Pacey like its MY boyfriend/bestfriend/whatever.  Im bordering on the edge of obsessed and its digusting.  It all started my junior year when I had a little Dawson-Joey-Pacey love triangle of my own going on.  I used it as a crutch to get through my worst time...well one of them.  And now its like I gave birth to the damn show or something.  It could be Chad Michael Murray (Charlie) who is totally and completely undeniable gorgeous that is making me so emotional over Dawson's too.  When ever I watch it I get this horrible feeling in my gut.  Like when someone dumps you.  It really sucks.  I balled like a baby when Dawson and Jen broke up last week.  I am totally rooting for Joey and Charlie.  I am torn with Pacey and Audrey.  I like them both but I am crushed that Pacey and Joey arent together anymore because face it - they are perfect for eachother.  2 wild children dont belong together.  MAYBE just maybe Dawson should be with Audrey and Joey still with Pacey.  I will give Joey and Pacey props though for remaining friends.  We really dont know what is going on with Jack lately.  Which is really too bad.  I like him for Daniel's sake.  (sigh.  I miss you best friend).  

I think that Dawson and his little group of friends remind me of my friends in Spain a little.  I missed them so much.  I am so glad to just be reconnecting with them.  Unfortunately I've already missed out on 3 years of there lives.  They were my first group of real friends.  If I was to assign them characters (well first off I would have to group like 3 of them in 1 person) but they would be: I of course am Dawson, Joey would be Andrea cuz she's still my best friend, Pacey would be Jimmy and Butch, Audrey would be Shavonne, and all the others that I really dont keep in touch with that much  would be Andi because we never hear about her.  (Actually I didnt like Andi but that doesnt mean that the ppl I clumped with her I dont like.  Au contrair.  I LOVE my friends!)  I would have to make up a whole new character for Megan Horry though.  I would call her Celeste.  I dont know why I just would.
hmm.  Rambling on about Dawsons Creek.  At least I feel a little better.
heh.  Dont get me started on Felicity...
